  "original_title": "\u0baa\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0bb3\u0bc1\u0bae\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0b8a\u0b9f\u0bbe\u0b95 \u0baa\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b9c\u0ba9\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baa\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bc8 \u0ba4\u0bc6\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0bc1 \u0b9a\u0bc6\u0baf\u0bcd\u0baf\u0bc1\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd : \u0b9a\u0bc1\u0baf\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bc0\u0ba9 \u0b85\u0bb0\u0b9a\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b95\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0bb2\u0bc8\u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0b9a\u0baa\u0bbe\u0ba8\u0bbe\u0baf\u0b95\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0b9f\u0bae\u0bcd \u0bb5\u0bb2\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bc1\u0bb1\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bb2\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Elect President through Parliament: Independent Political Party Leaders urge Speaker",
      "author": "Digital Desk 5",
      "body_lines": [
        "Realizing the serious nature that the country is facing, attention should also be paid to electing the President through the Parliament. Leader of the Lanka Samasamaja Party Prof. Tissa Vidharana said that if the parliament does not act according to the expectations of the people, the people will besiege the parliament.",
        "The people's peaceful struggle against the government has been 100 percent successful. President Gotabaya Rajapaksa should understand that he does not have a Lok Sabha and step down in a civilized manner.",
        "The common people have fulfilled their responsibility. The people's representatives at the parliamentary level should fulfill their responsibility. They should elect the answerable president through the parliament and fulfill the expectations of the people.",
        "The 225 members of parliament should understand that if the current crisis is not resolved through the parliament, the people will besiege the parliament, so all parties except the president should come together to resolve the current crisis.",
        "It is gratifying that the people's struggle has been successful. We respect the people of the country for expressing their basic rights democratically in a non-violent manner."
      ],
